L: Thanks for the details — this helps a lot. Here’s a refined breakdown based on that exact description:

⸻

🍝 Dinner: Fresh Tagliatelle with Traditional Beef, Veal & Pork Ragu

With 36-month Parmigiano Reggiano and EVOO

Estimated Nutritional Info (Restaurant Portion):
Nutrient Estimate
Calories ~800–950 kcal
Protein ~35–45g
Carbohydrates ~60–70g (mostly from fresh pasta)
Fat ~35–45g (from meat blend, cheese, EVOO)
Saturated Fat ~12–18g
Fiber ~3–5g
Sodium ~1000–1400mg

⸻

⚠️ Health Notes (Based on Your Profile):
Factor Notes
Fatty Liver ⚠️ Moderate-to-high in saturated fat — not ideal if frequent, but okay as an occasional indulgence. EVOO is a plus.
Cholesterol Watch ⚠️ From veal, pork, beef, and cheese — not a daily item.
Blood Sugar / Carbs ⚠️ Fresh tagliatelle is refined carb-heavy; pairing with protein and fat helps blunt sugar spike.
Sodium ⚠️ On the high side with aged cheese and ragu base.

⸻

✅ Lightening It Next Time (If Needed):
• Ask for a half-portion or share it.
• Balance with a side salad, water, and limit other high-fat/sodium meals that day.
• Consider skipping bread if it’s served with it.

Let me know if you want to log it as the full entrée, or if you ate less than that.

